Rating: 3
Decidedly good as written, possibly a bit higher than three stars. With some modifications it becomes even better. As mentioned by another reviewer I diced and added a yukon gold initially for body and I used about 1 1/2 lbs. of chicken breasts instead of the thigh meat. I increased the curry powder to 3 tsps. initially to give it the kick that it needed. After adding the puree and stock and simmering for about 10 minutes I added somewhere between 2 and 3 handfulls of fresh baby spinach (for texture and color). When I tasted the final result I was quite pleased but not entirely satisfied and so I finished it off with perhaps a 1/2 can of light coconut milk and an additional 1/2 tsp of curry powder. This soup I would give 3 1/2 stars.

