There was a time, not too long ago, that putting together this delightful soup would have been an enjoyable evening pastime. Since the birth of my daughter, cooking weekday meals has become a bit more chaotic, and the phrase "Too busy to cook" has taken on a whole new meaning. It took me about an hour, start to finish, to put this beautiful soup on the table. It was definitely worth the time and effort. I chopped the onions and the carrots finely in the food processor, but I cubed the chicken by hand. The bits of chicken were juicy, rather like little dumplings. The final texture and look of the soup was very appealing and rather elegant, but still hearty enough for a main course.

